  "response_text": "A waitress in a bright, retro-looking diner stands behind the counter holding a turquoise-blue box of Triples cereal upright so its front faces out. The box has large white “Triples” lettering, curved rainbow-like stripes, and a picture of golden cereal pieces near the bottom. The waitress is a light-skinned adult woman with short reddish-blonde hair, a pink headband, small hoop earrings, and a pink uniform dress with a white collar and white sleeve cuffs. Around her are shiny diner fixtures: shelves with dishes, a round glowing light or mirror behind her, metal appliances, and jars on the counter. Another worker in a similar pale pink uniform moves in the background. The waitress turns her head toward someone off to her left, leaning slightly over the counter with a confident, expectant expression while keeping the cereal box visible in front of her.\n\nAcross the counter sit three customers in a booth-like diner setting with red seating, curtained windows, wall lights, and menus. In the center is a heavyset, middle-aged light-skinned man in a loose light-blue button-up shirt. A small white bowl sits in front of him. On his left is a younger-looking person with short dark hair, mostly hidden behind a menu; on his right is a blonde adult woman holding a large menu upright. Both side customers look calm and reserved while the man in the center looks straight ahead, expression flat and unimpressed.\n\nThe commercial then moves into a clean product-comparison display on a plain white background. A blue Kellogg’s Rice Krispies box appears at the right, with large white “RICE KRISPIES” text and the familiar cartoon characters on the front. Along the bottom, small black legal text reads, “Rice Krispies is a registered trademark of the Kellogg Co.” A blue bowl filled with pale yellow cereal pieces slides into view on the left as the Rice Krispies box moves aside. Soon a second blue bowl appears to the right, filled with a darker golden cereal. A third blue bowl then rises into the foreground below them, filled with chunkier golden pieces. The three bowls arrange themselves like a triangle: two bowls higher in the background and one larger bowl lower in front. They then visually blend together into a single blue bowl filled with mixed golden cereal pieces, representing the combination in Triples.\n\nBack in the diner, the waitress rests her cheek on one hand behind the counter, watching with a small, knowing smile. Behind her are glass display cases and shelves with dishes and food items, softly lit in warm colors. The man in the blue shirt now eats from the bowl in front of him, with the Triples box standing on the counter to his left. He leans down over the bowl, takes a bite, and begins to react. His head dips, then he moves closer and closer, his face filling the view. His expression changes from concentration to surprise: his eyebrows lift, his eyes open wide, and he stares ahead with an exaggerated, comic look of discovery.\n\nThe view widens again to the diner counter. The man has turned around on his stool, facing away from the counter toward the red booths behind him, as if doing a dramatic double take. The younger person and the blonde woman beside him remain mostly still behind their menus, while the Triples box, the bowl, a white mug, metal napkin holder, and condiment bottles sit along the counter. A brief layered transition shows the waitress over the diner scene, reinforcing that she is watching his reaction. She then appears close up, still in her pink uniform and headband, holding one hand near her face. She glances to the side with a satisfied, unsurprised expression, as though the man’s reaction is exactly what she expected.\n\nFinally, the three customers are shown together at the counter again. The Triples box stands prominently in the foreground on the left, front label facing out. The man in the blue shirt sits centered, smiling slightly now, with his bowl in front of him. The two people beside him continue holding menus, but their eyes angle toward him. The diner setting remains bright and orderly, with red booths, curtained windows, and counter items framing the product and the customer’s pleased reaction.",
